<i>adjective</i>: 달갑다 [달갑따] <i>adverb</i>: 어서어서 [어서어서] <i>noun</i>: 환영 [화녕] <i>verb</i>: 환영하다 [화녕하다], 대환영하다 [대ː화녕하다] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>adjective</i><br>
<dt>달갑다 [달갑따]</dt><br>
<dd>welcome; satisfactory</dd><br>
<dd>마음에 들어 만족스럽다.</dd><br>
<dd>Feeling satisfied with something because it suits one's taste.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt>어서어서 [어서어서]</dt><br>
<dd>1. without delay; fast; promptly</dd><br>
<dd>일이나 행동을 아주 빨리 하도록 재촉하는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An adverb used to urge someone to act or do something very quickly.</dd><br>
<dd>2. right; welcome; please</dd><br>
<dd>매우 반갑게 맞아들이거나 매우 간절히 권하는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An adverb used to welcome someone or offer him/her something very eagerly.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>환영 [화녕]</dt><br>
<dd>welcome</dd><br>
<dd>오는 사람을 기쁘고 반갑게 맞이함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of receiving someone gladly and cordially upon his/her arrival.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>verb</i><br>
<dt>환영하다 [화녕하다]</dt><br>
<dd>welcome; greet</dd><br>
<dd>오는 사람을 기쁘고 반갑게 맞이하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To receive someone arriving gladly and cordially.</dd><br>
<dt>대환영하다 [대ː화녕하다]</dt><br>
<dd>welcome</dd><br>
<dd>크게 환영하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To welcome someone in a grand manner.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>